---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Oil Rig Jobs & Careers — Roles, Hierarchy, Salary"
  description="Complete guide to oil rig careers: every role from roustabout to toolpusher, salary ranges, required certifications, and the full progression path."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Careers', href: '/careers' }]}
  lang="en"
  alternateHref="/es/careers"
>
  <Nav slot="nav" lang="en" alternateHref="/es/careers" />
  <Footer slot="footer" lang="en" />

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-eyebrow">03 — People</div>
    <h1>Rig <span>Careers</span></h1>
    <p class="page-hero-sub">Every position on a rig, what it pays, and how to get there. No experience required to start — just the willingness to learn from the ground up.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="block">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Guides</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Career <span>Guides</span></h2>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-icon">🪜</span>
        <h3>How to Become a Roughneck</h3>
        <p>The complete entry-level path — no experience needed. Certifications, physical requirements, and how to actually get hired.</p>
        <a href="/careers/roughneck" class="card-link">Read the Guide →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-icon">🎛️</span>
        <h3>How to Become a Driller</h3>
        <p>The path from floorhand to running the console. What IWCF levels you need and how long it really takes.</p>
        <a href="/careers/driller" class="card-link">Read the Guide →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-icon">🔥</span>
        <h3>How to Become a Rig Welder</h3>
        <p>Welding certifications, process qualifications, and the path to underwater welding or CWI inspector.</p>
        <a href="/welding/certifications" class="card-link">Read the Guide →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-icon">💰</span>
        <h3>Oil Rig Salary Guide</h3>
        <p>Real pay ranges for every position, onshore vs offshore, and how day rates and rotations affect take-home pay.</p>
        <a href="/careers/salary" class="card-link">See Salaries →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-icon">📜</span>
        <h3>Certifications Explained</h3>
        <p>BOSIET, IWCF, NEBOSH, H₂S — what each certification covers and which roles require them.</p>
        <a href="/careers/certifications" class="card-link">See Certifications →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-icon">🌊</span>
        <h3>Offshore vs Onshore</h3>
        <p>Pay differences, rotation schedules, lifestyle tradeoffs, and how to decide which path fits you.</p>
        <a href="/careers/salary#offshore-vs-onshore" class="card-link">Compare →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Overview</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Rig <span>Hierarchy</span></h2>
    <p style="color:var(--fog);max-width:640px;margin-bottom:32px;">Every person on a rig has a specific function. Drilling crews operate in 8- or 12-hour tours (shifts), with clear lines of authority from floorhand to company man.</p>

    <div class="hierarchy">
      <div class="hier-row header">
        <span>Position</span><span>Responsibilities</span><span>Pay Range (US)</span><span>Experience</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hier-row">
        <div><span class="role-name">Company Man</span><span class="role-level">Client Rep</span></div>
        <div class="role-desc">On-site representative of the oil company funding operations. Final authority on well program decisions.</div>
        <div class="role-pay">$150K–$300K</div>
        <div class="role-exp">15+ yrs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hier-row">
        <div><span class="role-name">Toolpusher</span><span class="role-level">Rig Supervisor</span></div>
        <div class="role-desc">Overall supervisor of rig contractor's operations. Manages all crews, tools, and equipment.</div>
        <div class="role-pay">$90K–$180K</div>
        <div class="role-exp">10–15 yrs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hier-row">
        <div><span class="role-name"><a href="/careers/driller" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;">Driller</a></span><span class="role-level">Crew Supervisor</span></div>
        <div class="role-desc">Controls drilling from the console. Monitors WOB, RPM, torque, pump pressure. Supervises the crew.</div>
        <div class="role-pay">$70K–$120K</div>
        <div class="role-exp">5–8 yrs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hier-row">
        <div><span class="role-name">Derrickman</span><span class="role-level">Specialist</span></div>
        <div class="role-desc">Works the monkey board 90–100 ft up guiding pipe stands. Operates mud pumps and monitors pit volumes.</div>
        <div class="role-pay">$55K–$90K</div>
        <div class="role-exp">3–5 yrs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hier-row">
        <div><span class="role-name"><a href="/careers/roughneck" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;">Roughneck</a></span><span class="role-level">Rig Floor Crew</span></div>
        <div class="role-desc">Makes up/breaks out pipe connections. Operates the catwalk. The backbone of drilling operations.</div>
        <div class="role-pay">$45K–$70K</div>
        <div class="role-exp">1–3 yrs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hier-row">
        <div><span class="role-name">Roustabout</span><span class="role-level">Entry Level</span></div>
        <div class="role-desc">General labor: painting, cleaning, moving supplies, assisting crane operations. Entry point for most careers.</div>
        <div class="role-pay">$38K–$55K</div>
        <div class="role-exp">No exp required</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
